Take a quick peek at the sidebar to ensure that you’re in the Summary section of your iPhone’s settings. Now scroll down to the Options section on the right and check the box for Open iTunes when this iPod is connected. Remember to click on the Apply button to confirm the change. And problem solved![/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row]
